Java String class methods:

The java.lang.String class provides many useful methods to perform operation on sequence of char value.

1. char charAt(int index): returns char value for the particular index
2. int length(): returns string length
3. static String format(String format, Object... args): returns a formatted string
4. static String format(Locale I, String format, Object... args): returns formatted string with given locale.
5. String subString(int beginIndex): returns substring for given begin index.
6. String subString(int beginIndex, int endIndex): returns substring for the given begin index and end index.
7. boolean contains(CharSequence s): returns true or false after matching the sequence of char value.
8. satic String join(charSequence delimiter, CharSequence..elements): returns a joined string.
9. boolean equals(Object another): checks the quality of string with given object.
10. boolean isEmpty(): checks if string is empty or note
11. String concat(String str): concatenates the specified string
12. String replace(char old, char new): replaces all occurrences of the specified char value.
13. String replace(CharSequence old, CharSequence new): replaces all occurrences of the specified CharSequence.
14. static String equalsIgnoreCase(String another): compares with another String and dosen't check case of String.
15. String[] split(String regx): returns a split string matching regx.
16. String[] split(String regx, int limit): returns a split string matching regx and limit.
17. String intern(): returns an interned string.
18. int indexOf(int ch, int fromindex): returns the specified char value index starting from given index.
19. int indexOf(String substring): returns the specified substring index.
20. int indexOf(String substring, int fromIndex): returns the specified substring index starting with given index.
21. String toLowerCase(): returns a string in lowercase
22. String toLowerCase(Locale I): returns a string in lowercase using specified locale.
23. String trim(): removes beginning and ending spaces of the string.
24. static String valueOf(int value): converts given type imto String. It is an Overloaded method.